An '''arming plug''' is a small plug that is fitted into [[flight hardware]] to enable functions that, for instrument or personnel safety, should not be activated before flight.  In the case of a [[missile]] or [[bomb]], the (lack of the) arming plug prevents [[explosion]] before flight; in the case of a [[spacecraft]] or scientific [[sounding rocket]], it might prevent premature firing of a [[hydrazine]] thruster system (hydrazine is extremely toxic) or block [[cryogenic]] or [[photographic film]] systems from operating before [[Rocket launch|launch]].

