A '''tree planting bar''' or '''dibble bar'''<ref>{{cite book |first=Mary L. |last=Duryea |author2=Philip M. Dougherty |title=Forest Regeneration Manual |publisher=Kluwer Academic Publishers |year=1991 |isbn=978-07923-0959-8 |page=311}}</ref> is a [[tool]] used by [[forester]]s to [[tree planting|plant tree]]s, especially in large-scale [[afforestation]] or [[reforestation]]. It is very [[ergonomy|ergonomic]], as it greatly speeds up the planting and prevents [[back pain]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mmbqdm.tripod.com/ForestManagement/OakTreePlantings.htm |first=Leon E. |last=Hank |title=Success in Oak Tree Plantings}}</ref>
